The organisation gives an overall positive assessment of Malta's implementation process of all the seven flagship flagship initiatives that published earlier this year, although the report notes that some initiatives could do with more time to deliver real progress. The government said Malta had achieved good progress for all their flagship programmes - and said the Monitoring Platform's main beneficial outcome was that it keeps an eye on the status of major economic policies of the EU 2020 Strategy. Xavier Sol, the government's spokesman, noted in a statement that Malta's 20 priorities mostly aim at reforming existing policies to achieve greater efficiency and to generate economic growth. "It is well known that the main challenges Malta faces in terms of employment, reforms, competitiveness and sustainability are leaing forces of promoting private sector and knowledge spending.."
